  "text": "Let V(x, t) denote the reproductive value of an individual with reserves x at time t, given that behaviour is optimal. The function V specifies the expected future reproductive success of the animal and is the current value of the animal's life [CITATION_1] . The rate at which reproductive value increases with increasing energy reserves, vV/vx, measures the value, in terms of future reproductive success, of an increase in reserves. The ratio of this marginal value of food to the value of life,",
